summary:
Mufasa: The Lion King Box Office Collection Day 3 (Updated Live)

Publication Date: December 21, 2023, Source: Times of India

Disney's new animated musical drama Mufasa: The Lion King, a prequel to The Lion King, experienced notable growth at the box office on Sunday, inching closer to the Rs 50 crore mark.

  • The film earned approximately Rs 18.75 crore on Sunday.
  • Its total net collection stands at around Rs 41.25 crore after three days.
  • Mufasa opened with Rs 8.8 crore, with Rs 3.5 crore from English screenings.
  • Shah Rukh Khan voices a character in the Hindi-dubbed version, contributing Rs 2.6 crore to the total.
  • In North America, it grossed $35 million over the weekend, below the estimated $50 million.
  • The film debuted in 4,100 theaters, dominating most IMAX screens.
“Despite the underwhelming start, analysts predict a strong run, with schoolchildren now on year-end vacations in North America.”

Despite falling short of the Rs 50 crore mark expected for a blockbuster, Mufasa is being celebrated as part of Disney's strongest annual performance, contributing to over $5 billion in global ticket sales.
